    "description": "## How to Use This Collection\n\n1. Set the `base_url` variable to your application's base URL (default is http://localhost:8000)\n2. The collection includes 3 endpoints:\n   - Subscribe to Website (POST /api/subscribe)\n   - Create Post (POST /api/posts)\n   - List Websites (GET /api/websites)\n\n## Requirements\n\n- PHP 8.0+\n- MySQL 5.7+\n- Redis (for queue processing)\n\n## Setup Instructions\n\n```bash\n# Clone the repository\ngit clone https://github.com/yourusername/subscription-platform.git\ncd subscription-platform\n\n# Install dependencies\ncomposer install\n\n# Configure environment\ncp .env.example .env\nphp artisan key:generate\n\n# Update .env with your database credentials\nDB_CONNECTION=mysql\nDB_HOST=127.0.0.1\nDB_PORT=3306\nDB_DATABASE=subscription_platform\nDB_USERNAME=root\nDB_PASSWORD=\n\n# Set queue connection\nQUEUE_CONNECTION=redis\n\n# Run migrations and seeders\nphp artisan migrate --seed\n\n# Start the development server\nphp artisan serve\n\n# In a separate terminal, start the queue worker\nphp artisan queue:work\n```\n\n## Key Features\n\n- RESTful API for subscription management\n- Background email processing using queues\n- Prevention of duplicate email notifications\n- Validation for all API inputs\n- Seeded website data for testing\n\n## Scheduled Command\n\nThe email sending command should be scheduled to run periodically:\n\n```bash\n# Add to cron schedule\n* * * * * cd /path-to-project && php artisan schedule:run >> /dev/null 2>&1\n```\n\nIn `app/Console/Kernel.php`:\n\n```php\nprotected function schedule(Schedule $schedule)\n{\n    $schedule->command('subscriptions:send-emails')->everyMinute();\n}\n```\n\n## Testing\n\nUse the provided Postman collection to test all endpoints. The seeded websites have IDs 1, 2, and 3."
